{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01RzMjKqXRDcxC9iQpX2gGZa","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Done. Here's what was done and why it works:\n\n**Problem:** The replica set had 2 voters (mongo-rs-0, mongo-rs-1). With only 2 votes, a majority requires both nodes — losing either one means no quorum, no election, no primary.\n\n**Solution:** Added `mongo-arb-0` as an arbiter member:\n- `arbiterOnly=true` — holds no data, no storage cost\n- `votes=1` — provides the tiebreaking 3rd vote\n- `priority=0` — can never become primary\n\n**Result:** 3 votes total, majority = 2. Either data-bearing member can now fail and the surviving node can still win an election with the arbiter's vote.\n\n**Prerequisite step:** MongoDB 5+ refuses to reconfig if it would silently change the implicit default write concern. Setting `defaultWriteConcern: {w: \"majority\"}` explicitly before `rs.addArb()` satisfies that guard.\n\n**Data integrity:** `app.test` still has 3 documents — unchanged."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":300,"cache_read_input_tokens":34810,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":300},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"26333cd8-d8f5-406a-919d-ba5a65d0b60e","uuid":"1d25a974-c482-4768-92a0-0f27a370fc00","request_id":"req_011CcQ5VXFiUoDp5VbrRauRs"}
